CRITICAL IFRAME EXECUTION RULES (MANDATORY):

- The application may use nested, dynamic, or changing iframes.
- NEVER directly interact with page using:
    page.click(), page.fill(), page.press(), page.locator(), page.get_by*().
- For EVERY user interaction:
    ctx = resolve_context(page, "<selector>")
    ctx.click / ctx.fill / ctx.press must be used.
- resolve_context(page, selector) will be provided at runtime.
- Do NOT cache frame references.
- Do NOT use page.frames[index].
- Iframes may change after navigation; always resolve context again per step.

NAVIGATION RULES:

- If an action causes navigation or page change:
    - wait using page.wait_for_load_state("networkidle")
      OR wait for the next required selector using resolve_context.
- Do NOT use time.sleep() except where explicitly instructed.

SELECTOR RULES (MANDATORY):

- DO NOT use XPath with contains(text()).
- DO NOT assume elements are <a> tags.
- Prefer Playwright accessibility selectors:
    get_by_role("link", name="...")
    get_by_role("button", name="...")
    get_by_role("menuitem", name="...")
- If text-based selection is required, use:
    get_by_role or get_by_text (exact match).
- Only use XPath if no role-based selector is possible.
